HEADWORD: Foumart
<hw>Fou"mart`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>folmard</ets>, <ets>fulmard</ets>; AS. <ets>f⟦umac⟧l</ets> foul +
<ets>mear⟦edh⟧</ets>, <ets>meard</ets>, marten: cf. F. <ets>marte</ets>,
<ets>martre</ets>. See <er>Foul</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and <er>Marten</er>
the quadruped.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European polecat; --
called also <altname>European ferret</altname>, and
<altname>fitchew</altname>. See <er>Polecat</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>foulmart</asp>, <asp>foulimart</asp>, and
<asp>fulimart</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

